-- Arava Signs Israel's First Solar Project Financing Loan for $26 Million
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2010-12-13T10:02:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-13/arava-signs-israel-s-first-solar-project-financing-loan-for-26-million.html
Arava Power Co. signed a loan
agreement with Bank Hapoalim BM for a $26 million photovoltaic
plant in Israel, the first solar project financing in the
country.  The Israeli renewable energy developer raised about $20.8
million in debt for a 4.9-megawatt photovoltaic park at Kibbutz
Kitura, the company said today in an e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
